topics.body:
So AirAsia may have been found; they've found several bodies floating along with luggage and such.  Probably they're all dead, but at least their families will have closure.

Also senate whip Steve Scalise is currently under fire because it turns out he spoke at a white supremacist convention in 2002.  The reason why he's under fire is because he a year after attending said he agreed with their "conservative" ideology; foot meet mouth, mouth meet foot.
topics.author: 38b55cdf63616403d7560600

topics.body:
They've found wreckage of the AirAsia flight.  40 bodies have been found, but not the plane yet.

Also the 5th circuit appeals court is to hear arguments on same-sex marriage for Texas, Louisiana and Missippi.  One judge will most definitely vote no on repealing; one judge will most definitely vote yes on repealing the ban; the last judge is center left so there's a slight chance in favor of repeal.  The question is how long will it take?
